Super Bowl all-time record book

  • Published
    4 February 2025

The NFL Super Bowl is the biggest game in American sport and one of the biggest events on the planet.

Every year 32 teams battle it out for the chance to make it to the big game, with everything on the line in just 60 minutes to find out who will lift the Vince Lombardi Trophy.

But who has stood out in the long, rich history of the Super Bowl? Who holds all the major records for the best and worst performances in the big game.

Let's find out.

Super Bowl career records

  • Super Bowls as a player: 10 Tom Brady

  • Wins by a player: 7 Tom Brady

  • Super Bowls as a head coach: 9 Bill Belichick

  • Wins by a head coach: 6 Bill Belichick

  • Completed passes: 277 Tom Brady

  • Passing yards: 3,039 Tom Brady

  • Touchdown passes: 21 Tom Brady

  • Interceptions: 8 John Elway

  • Touchdowns scored: 8 Jerry Rice

  • Receiving touchdowns: 8 Jerry Rice

  • Rushing touchdowns: 5 Emmitt Smith

  • Rushing yards: 354 Franco Harris

  • Receiving yards: 589 Jerry Rice

Super Bowl single game player records

  • Touchdowns scored: 3 Jerry Rice, Roger Craig, Ricky Watters, Terrell Davis, James White, Jalen Hurts

  • Completed passes: 43 Tom Brady (Patriots v Falcons 2017)

  • Passing yards: 505 Tom Brady (Patriots v Eagles 2018)

  • Touchdown passes: 6 Steve Young (49ers v Chargers 1995)

  • Interceptions thrown: 5 Rich Gannon (Raiders v Buccaneers 2003)

  • Rushing touchdowns: 3 Terrell David (Broncos 1998) Jalen Hurts (Eagles 2023)

  • Rushing yards: 204 Timmy Smith (204 for Washington v Denver 1988)

  • Catches: 14 James White (Patriots v Falcons 2017)

  • Receiving yards: 215 Jerry Rice (49ers v Bengals 1989)

  • Receiving touchdowns: 3 Jerry Rice (49er v Broncos 1990, v Chargers 1995)

  • Interceptions: 3 Rod Martin (Raiders v Eagles 1981)

  • Pick sixes: 2 Dwight Smith (Buccaneers v Raiders 2003)

  • Tackles: 18 Dan Morgan (Panthers v Patriots 2004)

  • Sacks: 3 Reggie White (Packers 1997), Darnell Dockett (Cardinals 2009), Kony Ealy (Panthers 2016), Grady Jarrett (Falcons 2017)

Longest plays in Super Bowl history

  • Receiving touchdown: 85 yards Jake Delhomme to Muhsin Muhammad (Panthers v Patriots 2004)

  • Rushing touchdown: 75 yards Willie Parker (Steelers v Seahawks 2006)

  • Field goal: 57 yards Harrison Butker (Chiefs v 49ers 2024)

  • Interception return touchdown: 100 yards James Harrison (Steelers v Cardinals 2009)

  • Fumble return touchdown: 49 yards Mike Bass (Washington v Miami 1973)

  • Kick-off return touchdown: 108 yards Jacoby Jones (Ravens v 49ers 2013)

  • Punt return*: 65 yards Kadarius Toney (Chiefs v Eagles 2023)

  • *There has never been a punt return touchdown in Super Bowl history

Super Bowl game records

  • Highest scoring Super Bowl: 49ers 49-26 Chargers 1995

  • Lowest scoring Super Bowl: Patriots 13-3 Rams 2019

  • Most points scored by a team: 55 (49ers 55-10 Broncos 1990)

  • Fewest points scored by a team: 3 (Dolphins 3-24 Cowboys 1972, Rams 3-13 Patriots 2019)

  • Biggest margin of victory: 45 (49ers 55-10 Broncos 1990)

  • Biggest comeback: 25pts (3-28) Patriots 34-28 Falcons 2017

  • Most team yards: 613 Patriots (v Eagles 2018)

  • Most total yards: 1,151 (Patriots v Eagles 2018)

  • Most turnovers by a team: 9 Bills (v Cowboys 1993)

  • Total field goals in a game: 7 (Chiefs v 49ers 2024)

  • Total sacks in a game: 12 (Broncos v Panthers 2016)
